trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of instances of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> class.
This class cannot be inherited.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection"></xref> class.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> to the end of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> to add to the collection.
The zero-based index where the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> parameter has been added.
Returns a value indicating whether the specified <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> is a member of the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> for which to check collection membership.
if the serviceDescription parameter is a member of the ; otherwise, .

Copies the entire <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection"></xref> to a one-dimensional array of type <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref>, starting at the specified zero-based index of the target array.
An array of type <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> serving as the destination of the copy action.
The zero-based index at which to start placing the copied collection.

Searches the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection"></xref> and returns the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.Binding"></xref> with the specified name that is a member of one of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> instances contained in the collection.
An <xref:System.Xml.XmlQualifiedName> whose <xref:System.Xml.XmlQualifiedName.Name*> property is used to retrieve a <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.Binding"></xref> instance.
The binding with the specified name.

The specified <xref uid="langword_csharp_Service" name="Service" href=""></xref> is not a member of any <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> instances within the collection.
Searches for the specified <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> and returns the zero-based index of the first occurrence within the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> for which to search in the collection.
The zero-based index of the specified service description, or -1 if the element was not found in the collection.

Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> instance to the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection"></xref> at the specified zero-based index.
If the number of items in the collection already equals the collection's capacity, the capacity is doubled by automatically reallocating the internal array before the new element is inserted.

If the `index` parameter is equal to <xref:System.Collections.CollectionBase.Count%2A>, the `serviceDescription` parameter is added to the end of the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionCollection>.
The elements after the insertion point move down to accommodate the new element.
The zero-based index at which to insert the `serviceDescription` parameter.
The <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> to add to the collection.
Gets or sets the value of a <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> at the specified zero-based index.
The zero-based index of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> whose value is modified or returned.
The value of a <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> at the specified index.

A <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> specified by its namespace property.

Removes the first occurrence of the specified <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription"></xref> from the collection.
This method performs a linear search; therefore, the average execution time is proportional to <xref:System.Collections.CollectionBase.Count%2A>.
The elements that follow the removed <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescription> move up to occupy the vacated spot.
